{"title_page": "Oberoi Realty", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{COI|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Oberoi Realty Limited\n| logo = Oberoi Realty logo.svg\n| logo_size = 220px\n| type = [[Public Company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{BSE|533273}}<br />{{NSE|OBEROIRLTY}}\n| foundation = 1980\n| founder = \n| location = [[Mumbai]], [[India]]\n| key_people = Vikas Oberoi, Chairman and Managing director<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/report_wont-get-a-home-below-rs20-lakh-in-city_1214648 |title=Won\u2019t get a home below Rs20 lakh in city - Mumbai - DNA |publisher=Dnaindia.com |date=2008-12-17 |accessdate=2011-02-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/report_65-floor-fantasy-tower-will-rise-in-worli_1025979 |title=65-floor fantasy tower will rise in Worli - Mumbai - DNA |publisher=Dnaindia.com |date=2006-04-25 |accessdate=2011-02-02}}</ref>\n| industry = [[Real estate]]\n| products = [[Offices]] <br /> [[Apartments]]<br /> [[Shopping Malls]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.in/2008/06/11/stories/2008061151602100.htm |title=The Hindu Business Line : Oberoi Constructions enters retail space, opens mall in Mumbai |publisher=Thehindubusinessline.in |date=2008-06-11 |accessdate=2011-02-02}}</ref> <br /> [[Hotels]]\n| owner = \n| revenue = {{profit}} [[Indian rupee sign|\u20b9]] 2,66,124.69 lakh (2019)<ref>{{cite web|title=Oberoi Realty. Overview|url=https://www.bseindia.com/stock-share-price/oberoi-realty-ltd/oberoirlty/533273/|website=BSE|publisher=bseindia.com|accessdate=13 March 2020|ref=Oberoi Realty registered revenues of \u20b9 2,66,124.69 lakh}}</ref>\n| operating_income = {{profit}} [[Indian rupee sign|\u20b9]] 1,17,762.43 lakh (2019)\n| net_income = {{profit}} [[Indian rupee sign|\u20b9]] 81,693.35 lakh (2019)\n| assets = {{profit}} [[Indian rupee sign|\u20b9]] 11,12,853.62 lakh (2019)\n| homepage = [http://www.oberoirealty.com/ www.oberoirealty.com/]\n}}\n'''Oberoi Realty Limited''' one of the leading [[real estate development]] companies in India, is a family-owned business incorporated in 1998, it was earlier known as Oberoi Constructions Ltd. established by Mr. Ranvir Oberoi. Headquartered in [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]].<ref name=\"business-standard\">{{cite web|author=Raghavendra Kamath / Mumbai |url=http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/oberois-plan-rs-4000-cr-ipo/316695/ |title=Oberois plan Rs 4,000 cr IPO |publisher=Business-standard.com |date=2008-03-13 |accessdate=2011-02-02}}</ref>, India the company is listed on the [[Bombay Stock Exchange]] (BSE) and the [[National Stock Exchange]] (NSE) in 2010. Currently, it is headed by Mr. Vikas Oberoi, Chairman and Managing Director of the company.\n\nOberoi Realty began by developing premium residential projects and then diversified into commercial, hospitality, retail, and social infrastructure projects.\n\nThe company has currently 27.43 million square feet under construction. All these projects are spread across the island city of Mumbai that includes [[Worli]], Khar, [[Juhu]], [[Andheri]], [[JVLR]], [[Goregaon]], [[Kandivali]], [[Borivali]] in the western suburbs and [[Mulund]] and [[Thane]] in the central suburbs.\n\n==History==\nIt was incorporated in early 1980 as Oberoi Constructions which later changed to Oberoi Realty Limited. It was listed on [[Bombay Stock Exchange]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bseindia.com/bseplus/StockReach/AdvanceStockReach.aspx?scripcode=533273 |title=BSE Plus |publisher=Bseindia.com |date= |accessdate=2011-02-02}}</ref>\n\n==Notable projects==\n*Oberoi Garden City, [[Goregaon]] East, Mumbai is an award-winning flagship project of Oberoi Realty spread across 80 acres based on the concept \u201ccity within a city\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thepropertytimes.in/oberoi-realty-has-been-recognised-for-excellence-in-township-development-at-the-prestigious-ndtv-property-awards/|title=Excellence In Township Development award for Oberoi Garden City |work=NDTV Property Awards 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://rustomjeespaces.wordpress.com/2013/05/27/winners-of-realty-plus-excellence-awards-2013-west-announced-in-mumbai/|title=Integrated Township of the Year award for Oberoi Garden City |work=Realty Plus Excellence 2013}}</ref>. The development includes a mixed-use building comprising of a five-star hotel, The [[Westin]] Mumbai Garden City and Commerz a premium commercial office space; a first retail destination on the western side of Mumbai, Oberoi Mall; an IB School, [[Oberoi International School]] along with Commerz II which is a GOLD LEED-certified building. The project also includes [[residential developments]] such as Oberoi Seven, Oberoi Woods, Exquisite and Esquire. The company will be launching the 3rd phase of this project very soon.\n\n*[[Three Sixty West]], [[Worli]], is the first uber-luxury project developed by Oasis Realty - JV between Oberoi Realty and Sahana group; it is currently under construction. The development comprises of two towers - one houses The [[Ritz-Carlton Hotel]], and the other has luxury residences managed by The Ritz-Carlton.\n\n*Sky City by Oberoi Realty is a project being developed on a 25-acre land at [[Borivali]] East; bought from [[Tata Steel]] for Rs.1155 crores in 2014. The project will include multiple residential towers, a mall, and a hotel and is very close to the upcoming metro station.\n\n*Oberoi Realty also acquired a 60-acre land parcel from [[GlaxoSmithKline Pharmaceuticals]] in 2019 for Rs.890 crores that is yet to be launched.\n\n*Oberoi Splendor, a residential complex in [[Andheri East]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/ipo-issues-open/oberoi-realty-to-complete-4-major-parcelsnext-5-yrs_489175.html|title=Oberoi Realty to complete 4 major parcels in next 5 yrs|website=www.moneycontrol.com|access-date=2016-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.oberoirealty.com/properties-in-andheri/oberoi-splendor#!awards-and-accolades|title=Properties in Andheri  {{!}} Flats in Andheri East Mumbai {{!}} Oberoi Splendor|website=www.oberoirealty.com|access-date=2016-07-20}}</ref>\n\n*[[Three Sixty West]], the second tallest tower in India, is developed by Oberoi Realty.<ref>http://skyscrapercenter.com/create.php?list_status=COM&status_COM=on&status_UC=on&status_UCT=on&status_DEM=on&list_city=IN-BOM&search=yes</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n\n=== 2019 ===\n*Award for Three Sixty West under the category of '''Mixed-Use Development''' by Asia Pacific Property <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://propertyawards.net/asia-pacific-2019/|title=Three Sixty West wins Mixed-Use Development award|work=Asia Pacific Property 2019}}</ref>\n*Award for Esquire under the category of '''Residential High-Rise Development, India''' by Asia Pacific Property<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://propertyawards.net/asia-pacific-2019/|title=Esquire wins Residential High-Rise Development award|work=Asia Pacific Property 2019}}</ref>\n*'''Best Investor Relations Team (Mid-Cap), Oberoi Realty''' by IR Magazine Awards - India<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://events.irmagazine.com/indiaforum/wp-content/uploads/sites/76/2019/06/India-Awards-2019-Nominees-and-winners-V2.pdf|title=Oberoi Realty wins Best Investor Relations Team (Mid-Cap) award|work=IR Magazine Awards-India 2019}}</ref>\n*Achievement Award for '''Construction Health, Safety & Environment, Sky City''' by CIDC Vishwakarma Awards<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cidc.in/support/11thVishwakarma/Awardees%20List_11th%20VKA%202019%20(Final).pdf|title=Sky City wins Construction Health, Safety & Environment award|work=CIDC Vishwakarma Awards 2019}}</ref>\n*Achievement Award for New '''Standards in Construction Health, Safety & Environment, Three Sixty West''' by CIDC Vishwakarma Awards<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cidc.in/support/11thVishwakarma/Awardees%20List_11th%20VKA%202019%20(Final).pdf|title=Three Sixty West wins for New Standards in Construction Health, Safety &